==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water pocket
<hw>Water pocket</hw>. <def>A water hole in the bed of an intermittent
stream, esp. the bowl at the foot of a cliff over which the stream leaps
when in the flood stage.</def> <mark>[Western U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water poise</ent>⟦br⟧
